            <h2 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-bottom: 20px;">Dema Borî (Past Tenses)</h2>
            
            <div style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #333;">
                    Kurdish has <strong>two main past tenses</strong>: Simple Past (Dema Borî ya Hêsan) for completed actions in the past, 
                    and Past Perfect (Dema Borî ya Pêşketî) for actions that had happened before another past action.
                </p>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px;">1. Simple Past (Dema Borî ya Hêsan)</h3>
            
            <div style="background: #e8f5e9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 5px solid #2e7d32; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <h4 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-top: 0;">Usage:</h4>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8; color: #333; margin: 10px 0;">
                    Used for completed actions in the past.
                </p>
                <h4 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-top: 15px;">Formation:</h4>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8; color: #333; margin: 10px 0;">
                    Verb stem + past tense personal endings
                </p>
            </div>

            <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #666; margin-bottom: 30px; font-style: italic;">
